channel.title: Do you have 'assbergers'?
channel.description:
1) Go to http://glennrowe.net/BaronCohen/EmpathyQuotient/EmpathyQuotient.aspx 2) Take the quiz 3) Post results!
My result: 33.
The scale: 0 - 32 = low (most people with Asperger Syndrome or high-functioning autism score about 20) 33 - 52 = average (most women score about 47 and most men score about 42) 53 - 63 is above average 64 - 80 is very high 80 is maximum

item.title: Do you have 'assbergers'?
item.dc:creator: @The_Un-Named The Un-Named
item.description:
@The_Un-Named wrote:

Kidpaparoach:

For everyone saying this is bs, its not. The answer is inaccurate defonetly but with these things its hard to check if someone has it as people vary but theres only one set of questions so its a very general test…

well, it is bullshit, some of the questions asked are not related to aspergers at all and when they are it’s usually waaay off (see no. 5) and there’s just too many questions without any context given to give this test any credibility at all

I’d be wary of doing a quiz to diagnose an illness even if it’s a doctor who is asking the questions, many people who are suspected of having aspergers get sent off to a facility for a few weeks to have their behaviour observed by a doctor and then a diagnosis is given

Read full topic

item.title: Do you have 'assbergers'?
item.dc:creator: @amy_webb1 amy_webb
item.description:
@amy_webb1 wrote:

[quote=“ollie123, post:62, topic:433559”][quote author=amy_webb link=topic=536278.msg3923770#msg3923770 date=1329982938]

If you want to find out what it is like to have aspergers read, The curious incident of the dog in the night-time. An incredibly irritating book but it gives you the point of view of a kid with it.

I have friends who have been diagnosed with aspergers who are nothing like the kid in that book.

And i know people who have been diagnosed with aspergers who do.
[/quote]

That’s the problem. The symptoms under which they diagnose aspergers is too broad, and if the kid in that book (Christopher?) has aspergers, then my friend must be bullshitting.[/quote]
There are just more advanced people with aspergers, you can get different types that go up to high functioning and lower. Those who are higher seem more normal and just more sophisticated in curtain subjects rather then others.

Read full topic
